Each match in the IOC Grand Prix round robin is scored using the WBF's 30 point Victory Point scale. Canada beat the United states 34 IMPs to 5 IMPs in the first round and our 29 IMP win translated to 23 Victory Points for us and 7 for the United States.

It is always great to score as much as 23 Victory Points, but when you do it against one of the strongest bridge-playing countries in the world it is really something! Everyone congratulated Joey and I for making 5@H doubled and 7NT, but Nick and Peter had really done most of the hard work.

I believe that my "inexperienced" teammates learned a valuable lesson very early in this event - that they could beat anybody if they played well and received reasonable luck. Confidence is extremely important in this game. If you expect to lose then you are rarely disappointed. My team now knew that we were capable of beating the best, but there was an awfully long way to go....

